io.spine.protobuf

Interface ValidatingBuilder<M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - the type of the message to build
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, com.google.protobuf.Message.Builder, com.google.protobuf.MessageLite.Builder, com.google.protobuf.MessageLiteOrBuilder, com.google.protobuf.MessageOrBuilder

    @GeneratedMixin
public interface ValidatingBuilder<M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends com.google.protobuf.Message.Builder
    Implementation base for generated message builders.

    This interface defines a default method vBuild() which validates the built message before returning it to the user. In most cases, the users should use vBuild() and not the build(). If a user specifically needs to skip validation, they should use buildPartial() to make the intent explicit.
